    "ts": "2026-04-14T16:00:00+00:00",
    "headline": "UPS Seeks to Replace Manual Scans With Tracking Tech",
    "summary": "United Parcel Service is rolling out technology to more closely track the billions of small packages that move through its U.S. network each year.  The parcel-shipping giant said Tuesday it has invested $100 million to date to set up radio frequency identification, or RFID, technology across its network, with plans to spend more.  The company said the change will increase visibility throughout its small-package delivery network, while increasing delivery accuracy and reducing the manual labor needed to scan individual parcels.",
